  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A questionnaire will be used in order to find out the reasons for poor adherence for
      long-term treatment in children with asthma. The hypotheses is maternal factors including the
      knowledge that asthma is a chronic disease and fear to administer inhaled steroids are major
      obstacles for appropriate adherence.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Parents to children aged 2 - 12 years with moderate to severe asthma who need long-term
      treatment with inhaled steroids will be included in the study. Three weeks after their visit
      in the clinic, they will be requested to answer a questionnaire by telephone.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
